data.title: Find an Oregon Agency, Entity, or Local Jurisdiction : State of Oregon
data.meta_description: Oregon's state government is composed of three government branches: Executive, Legislative, and Judicial, as well as a system of commissions wherein citizens are appointed by the Governor and confirmed by the Senate.
